message.content: "cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV". The paper deals with neural reading comprehension models, which are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) community. The paper specifically focuses on the problem of undersensitivity, where models fail to consider important information in the input text. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of NLP, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV) (since reading comprehension models often involve visual inputs). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
